text:
BC CANNABIS STRIKE UPDATE - SUPPLY NOT AS PLENTIFUL 
-------------------------------
As of mid-October 2025, British Columbia is experiencing cannabis shortages due to an ongoing strike by the B.C. General Employees' Union (BCGEU) 
. The strike has shut down the province's central warehouse and delivery system, impacting both government-run and private cannabis retailers. 
Impact on cannabis supply 
Widespread closures: As of early October, the BCGEU had expanded its job action to include all government-run liquor and cannabis stores, warehouses, and headquarters. This effectively cut off supply to the majority of the province's cannabis retailers. 
Immediate effect on deliveries: The closure of the Liquor Distribution Branch (LDB) central warehouse in September halted all new deliveries from producers and stopped weekly shipments to retailers. 
Retailers feeling the pinch: Many private retailers are seeing their inventory dwindle after weeks of interrupted supply. Some shops, particularly smaller ones, are reporting they are running low on popular products like large-format flower and vapes. 
Customers turning to private stores: While the BC Cannabis Stores are closed, private retailers have seen an increase in customer traffic. However, their ability to meet demand is strained, and some are becoming overwhelmed. 
Past experience suggests long recovery: Following a similar, though shorter, BCGEU strike in 2022, it took the cannabis supply chain roughly three months to return to normal. Industry observers are predicting an even longer recovery time following this more extensive job action. [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8] 
What is providing some relief? 
The shortages are not as severe as they could be, thanks to several factors: 
Anticipation and preparation: Many private retailers, recalling the previous 2022 strike, stocked up on inventory in anticipation of the disruption. 
Direct Delivery program: British Columbia's Direct Delivery program allows smaller, licensed producers to sell their products directly to retailers, bypassing the government's central distribution system. This has served as a "relief valve" for some private shops, helping them to continue receiving at least some new stock. 
Increased Direct Delivery sales: The Direct Delivery program has seen a sharp increase in sales since the start of the strike, indicating its effectiveness in mitigating some of the supply disruption. [1, 7, 9, 10] 
What is being done to resolve the strike? 
Mediation initiated: On October 17, after seven weeks of the strike, the BC Government and the BCGEU agreed to enter into mediation. 

Continued job action: Despite the start of mediation, job action at the LDB warehouse and picket lines at BC Cannabis Stores are continuing for now. 

Union's position: The BCGEU is seeking a fair wage mandate for its members, citing concerns over the cost of living. 

Government's position: The government maintains that its wage offers are fiscally constrained and must be fair to both workers and taxpayers. [1, 6, 11, 12]  AI responses may include mistakes.

text:
üö®INDICTMENT ANALYSIS: WHO IS NEXT!?!üö®

‚ÄúComey. Bolton. The first dominoes have fallen. But this time, the counter-strike has a General.‚Äù

They came after General Michael Flynn with Crossfire Razor. They tried to end his career, his honor, his oath.

But history has a savage sense of irony...
The man they tried to silence is now advising Secretary of War Pete Hegseth and DNI Tulsi Gabbard inside the system that once targeted him.

And this time, he‚Äôs not the hunted, he‚Äôs one of the Hunters.

THE NEW INTEL FRONT

With Gabbard‚Äôs ODNI declassifying the Russia Hoax architecture and SOW Hegseth rebuilding the chain of command, the Trump-era Justice Department and military is quietly aligning the pieces of a massive internal correction.

No more sealed corridors.
No more ‚Äúanonymous sources.‚Äù
The truth has a timestamp now and it‚Äôs moving fast.

This isn‚Äôt politics.
It‚Äôs counter-insurgency within the bureaucracy.

THREE-FRONT STRATEGY

1. Operational Reform ‚Äì auditing and exposing the bureaucratic overlap between law enforcement, intelligence, and politics.
2. Contractor Transparency ‚Äì tracing how private ‚Äúfusion‚Äù firms blurred national security with partisan objectives.
3. Leak Accountability ‚Äì dismantling the media-intel pipelines that weaponized selective information against the American people.

THE SEVENTEEN TARGETS OF INDICTMENT
What comes next is no longer speculation, it‚Äôs pattern recognition.

Below: The 15 additional most likely next indictments based on proximity, exposure, and traceable fingerprints left inside the operation that tried to rewrite history and destroy America from within.

1. James Comey: FBI Director (2013‚Äì2017) - Central decision-maker who Authorized the Crossfire Hurricane investigation in July 2016. Fired by President Trump in 2017; his personal memos of meetings with the President triggered the appointment of Special Counsel Robert Mueller. ‚úÖ

2. John Bolton: National Security Adviser (2018‚Äì2019) - Publicly opposed Trump on foreign policy; relevant as example of alleged politicization of national-security deliberations and record handling, detailed in his 2020 memoir "The Room Where It Happened." ‚úÖ

3. Andrew McCabe: FBI Deputy Director - Supervised Crossfire Hurricane after Comey‚Äôs dismissal; referred for potential false-statement charges in 2018 (Justice Dept. declined prosecution).

4. Peter Strzok: FBI Counter-Intel Section Chief - Operational lead; 2016 text message, Strzok wrote, "No. No he won't. We'll stop it," in reference to Donald Trump's presidential campaign. This was part of a larger exchange with FBI lawyer Lisa Page that disparaged Trump and other political figures, which led to Strzok's firing in 2018.

5. Lisa Page: FBI Attorney - Legal conduit between investigators and senior counsel; texts and briefings show cross-level information flow. Resigned May 2018 before disciplinary hearing.

6. John Brennan: CIA Director - Oversaw CIA input to the Jan 2017 Intelligence Community Assessment (ICA) on Russian interference.  Questioned by Congress about analytic sourcing.

7. James Clapper: Director of National Intelligence - Coordinated the 2017 ICA; later testified about analytic confidence levels.

8. Susan Rice: National Security Adviser - Submitted ‚Äúunmasking‚Äù requests for certain intelligence reports in 2016‚Äì17; later defended them as routine national-security duties.

9. Samantha Power: U.N. Ambassador - Also associated with unmasking requests; helps map diffusion of sensitive SIGINT within diplomatic channels.

10. Bruce Ohr: DOJ Associate Deputy AG - Maintained contact with dossier author Christopher Steele after FBI cut ties; demoted 2017; retired 2020.

11. Nellie Ohr: Fusion GPS Researcher - Conducted open-source research on Russian figures for Fusion GPS.  Testified before House Oversight (Oct 2018). Wife of Bruce Ohr.

12. Glenn Simpson: Fusion GPS Co-Founder - Oversaw opposition-research project funded by DNC and Clinton campaign; testified before Senate Judiciary (2017).

13. Christopher Steele: Former MI6 Officer - Compiled the ‚ÄúSteele Dossier.‚Äù  Inspector-General report cited his reporting as unverified; FBI later cut ties.

14. James Baker: FBI General Counsel - Approved FISA paperwork and media-contact guidance; internal-legal precedent for process control.

15. Bill Priestap: FBI Counter-Intel Assistant Director Approved opening of Crossfire Hurricane (July 31 2016). Retired 2018.

16. Hillary Clinton: First Lady ('93-01), NY Senator (01-09), Secretary Of State ('09-'13) and Democratic Presidential Candidate (2016) - Clinton‚Äôs 2016 campaign and the DNC, through Perkins Coie, funded Fusion GPS and former British spy Christopher Steele to compile the now-infamous dossier on Donald Trump‚Äôs alleged Russia ties. The FBI launched Crossfire Hurricane months earlier on a separate foreign tip, later using parts of Steele‚Äôs unverified reports in FISA renewals and the related Crossfire Razor probe of Michael Flynn. Russia Hoax...

17. Barack Hussein Obama II: 44th President (2009-2017) Senator ('05-'08) - Barack Obama was president when U.S. intelligence first warned that Russia was interfering in the 2016 election, and his national-security team, including Comey, Clapper, and Brenna, briefed him as the FBI opened Crossfire Hurricane in July 2016. The January 2017 Intelligence Community Assessment (ICA), released under his watch, concluded Russia acted to aid Donald Trump, and Obama‚Äôs team reviewed and was aware of Michael Flynn‚Äôs contacts with the Russian ambassador before the transition. MAGA knows the Obama White House presided over a politicized intelligence posture that let opposition research and investigative momentum snowball into the ‚ÄúRussia Hoax‚Äù to defraud the American people!

THE DOCTRINE OF ACCOUNTABILITY

Gen. Flynn‚Äôs guiding philosophy can be summed up as ‚ÄúRestoring the Oath‚Äù a return to the sacred promise sworn by every soldier, agent and public servant: to defend the Constitution, not the bureaucracy that hides behind it.

Every decision, every reform, every act of oversight is measured by a single question:

‚ÄúDoes this strengthen the Republic or the bureaucracy?‚Äù

Under DNI Tulsi Gabbard, that doctrine has become operational.

Her ODNI teams are fusing declassification with reform, creating a transparent record of how politics infiltrated intelligence and how that infiltration ends under President Trump.

What was once buried in darkness and secrecy is being pulled into the sunlight.

This is not vengeance. It‚Äôs retribution, the deliberate reclamation of the Republic‚Äôs integrity and the oaths that built it.

FINAL THOUGHTS
America is watching the machine that once defined power devour itself. From Langley to Foggy Bottom, from contractor boardrooms to newsroom studios, the old playbook and old guard is collapsing under the weight of its own deception being exposed by President Trump.

A new doctrine is rising in its place:
Truth over politics. Oath over power. Republic over bureaucracy.

Flynn was the test case.
Now he‚Äôs the architect of the fix.
And the storm that once targeted him?
It‚Äôs reversing course.

Who are they saving the "Perp Walk" for? Your thoughts???

Semper Fi,
 -ALPHA

quote.text:
üá¨üáß When Did Britain Become This?

12,000 arrests a year for online speech. Let that sink in. The country that gave us free parliamentary debate, the land of "I disagree with what you say but defend your right to say it" ‚Äî now locking up housewives for memes and activists for angry tweets. More arrests than regimes London loves to lecture about human rights.

Section 127 of the Communications Act means 30 people arrested DAILY for being "grossly offensive" online. Not threats. Not actual crimes. Just opinions the state doesn't like. And after the 2024 riots? They went into overdrive. Most pleaded guilty under pressure, got sentences meant to "deter" others. Chilling effect? That's the whole point. Welcome to the new Britain, where your social media is a courtroom waiting to happen.

text:
Yemen Confirms Military Chief of Staff Killed in Israeli Strike

@LibertarianInst 

The Yemeni military revealed on Thursday that the chief of staff of the Ansarallah-led Yemeni Armed Forces (YAF), Major General Mohammed Abdul Kareem al-Ghamari, was killed by an Israeli strike. The statement said his 13-year-old son was also killed.

The official statement said Ghamari was killed ‚Äúwhile performing his jihadist duties,‚Äù and joined ‚Äúa large number of noble martyrs, civilian and military,‚Äù who were killed during the conflict with Israel. The statement did not say when he was killed.

Ansar Allah, the group that controls most of the populated areas of Yemen, launched a blockade of Israeli-linked shipping in 2023 in response to the genocide in Gaza. Ansar Allah has removed the blockade during ceasefire periods in Gaza.

Israel and the US have conducted large-scale bombing campaigns in Yemen over the past two years, but were unable to break the blockade. Additionally, Ansar Allah has attacked US ships in the Red Sea and targeted Israel with missiles and drones.

After weeks of the US bombing Yemen, in May, President Donald Trump reached a ceasefire with Ansar Allah that did not extend to Israel.

Israel and the US struck several civilian targets in Yemen, including ports, power plants, residential buildings, and media offices.
